    "name": "Max Martin",
    "profile": "Swedish pop-dance producer, musician, and songwriter, born on February 26, 1971 in Sånga, Ekerö, Uppland. \r\n\r\nMax Martin, who grew up in the urban settlement of Stenhamra in Sånga parish on the island of Färingsö in Ekerö Municipality, has been active both in Stockholm, Sweden and Los Angeles, California, and has created a series of international hits for commercially successful artists such as [a=Ace Of Base], [a=*NSYNC], [a=Britney Spears], [a=Katy Perry], [a=P!NK], [a=Usher], [a=The Weeknd], [a=Taylor Swift], [a=Céline Dion], and [a=Backstreet Boys].\r\n\r\nMax Martin formerly operated [l=Maratone Studios] with [a=Tom Talomaa] and now runs [l731678] in Stockholm, Sweden, as well as [l465221] in Stockholm, Sweden and [l=MXM Studios, Los Angeles] in California. [l265937] serves as his second primary tracking location.\r\n\r\n\r\n",
